The paper deals with the problem of computing a bi-Lipschitz embedding of a graphical metric into the line with minimum distortion, which is a problem in computational geometry and metric space theory. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) are the most likely categories. The paper also presents a bi-criteria approximation algorithm, which involves techniques from approximation algorithms and optimization, making cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) likely categories as well. Finally, the paper deals with metric spaces and embeddings, which are topics in mathematical sciences, making cs.MS (Mathematical Sciences) a possible category.
